cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of deep learning models and uncertainty estimation in medical applications, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on modeling uncertainty in deep learning models. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of deep learning models in medical imaging applications. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of deep learning models for quality control and referral systems. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of uncertainty estimation in natural language processing tasks. 

cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a less likely category, but possible as the paper discusses the use of deep learning models in medical imaging and multimedia applications.
